The South African Weather Service has issued a warning for severe weather conditions over parts of the Western Cape this weekend. Provincial Local Government Minister, Anton Bredell, says a cold front is expected to make landfall on Friday evening, bringing heavy downpours across the province on Saturday and Sunday. SA Weather | Friday 14 May 2021  He says the bulk of the rain is expected in the Overberg, Cape Agulhas and Swellendam areas. Four people were killed when heavy rains lashed the region last week. Western Cape Tomorrow ‘s Weather overview: 15.5.2021 pic.twitter.com/WQYAn1lBpU — SA Weather Service (@SAWeatherServic) May 14, 2021 